Odopoea diriangani
Distant, 1881
. The species has been collected in Nicaragua (
Metcalf 1963 a
) and Mexico (
Sanborn 2006 a
). The Mexican specimens were reported from Querétaro and Hidalgo (
Sanborn 2006 a
).

Miranha imbellis (
Walker, 1858
)
. The species is known from Mexico , Guatemala (
Metcalf 1963 a
) and Honduras (
Sanborn 2006 b
). The species has been reported from Chiapas (
Metcalf 1963 a
), Veracruz (
Sueur 2002
) and the author has identified specimens from Jalisco.

Diceroprocta alacris (
Stål, 1864
)
. The species is known only from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). Arizona and Texas specimens are considered to be later described species of
Diceroprocta
. Mexican specimens have been reported from Veracruz, Nuevo León, Tabasco and Yucatán (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has also identified specimens from Jalisco.

Diceroprocta bakeri (
Distant, 1911
)
. The species is known only from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The species has been reported to be collected in Morelos (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has also identified specimens from Veracruz.

Diceroprocta bulgara (Distant, 1906 )
. A species originally described from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
) with additional records from Guatemala (
Sanborn 2006 b
). It has been collected in Nayarit (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has identified specimens from Sinaloa, Jalisco, Sonora, Chihuahua, Colima, Oaxaca, Coahuila and Nayarit.

Diceroprocta crucifera (
Walker, 1850
)
. The species is only known from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). It has been reported from the Districto Federal (
Metcalf 1963 a
).

Diceroprocta digueti (Distant, 1906 )
. The species is known only from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). Specimens have been collected in Jalisco and Lower California (
Davis 1928
). The author has identified specimens from Baja California Norte and Baja California Sur.

Diceroprocta knighti (
Davis, 1917
)
. The species has been reported from Arizona , California and Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). Mexican specimens have been reported from Lower California and Sonora (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has also identified specimens from Sinaloa.

Diceroprocta ornea (
Walker, 1850
)
. The species is only known from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). It has been reported in Lower California, Sonora, Jalisco, and Puebla (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has also identified specimens from Chihuahua.

Diceroprocta psophis (
Walker, 1850
)
. The species is known only from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). It has been collected in Veracruz (
Metcalf 1963 a
).

Diceroprocta pusilla
Davis, 1942
. The species is described from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). It has also been reported from Guatemala and Honduras (
Sanborn 2006 b
). Mexican specimens are reported from Michoacán (
Davis 1942
). The author has identified specimens from Chiapas, San Luis Potosí, and Queretaro.

Diceroprocta texana (Davis, 1916 )
. The species is known from Texas, New Mexico , and Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). Mexican specimens were reported from Morelos (
Davis 1928
). The author has also identified specimens from Tamaulipas.

Diceroprocta virgulata (
Distant, 1904
)
. The species is known only from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
).

Tibicen montezuma (
Distant, 1881
)
. The species has been reported from Mexico , California, Arizona , New Mexico , Texas and Oklahoma (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The specimens from the United States are attributed to later described species of
Tibicen
(particularly
T. texanus Metcalf
) or misidentifications. The species appears to be an endemic Mexican species. It has been reported from Morelos in Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
).

Tibicen nigriventris (
Walker, 1858
)
. The species is known from Mexico , Costa Rica (
Metcalf 1963 a
), and Panama (
Wolda & Ramos 1992
). It has been reported from Veracruz in Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
).

Tibicen parallelus Davis, 1923
. The species is found in Arizona and New Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
) and Chihuahua (
Sanborn 2006 a
).

Cornuplura curvispinosa (
Davis, 1936
)
. The species is known only from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). Mexican specimens were reportedly collected in Colima and Jalisco (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has also identified specimens from Sinaloa and Nayarit.

Cacama crepitans (Van Duzee, 1914 )
. The species inhabits California and Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
). It has been reported from Baja California Sur, Espiritu Santo Island and San José Island (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has identified specimens from Baja California Norte and Baja California Sur.

Cacama longirostris (
Distant, 1881
)
. The species is only known from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
).

Cacama maura (
Distant, 1881
)
. The species is described from Mexico (
Metcalf 1963 a
) with additional records from Honduras (
Sanborn 2006 b
). Mexican specimens were collected in Morelos and Yucatán (
Metcalf 1963 a
). The author has also identified specimens from Oaxaca.

Beameria venosa (Uhler, 1888 )
. The species is found across much of the central and western United States (
Metcalf, 1963 a
). It has been reported from Chihuahua (
Sanborn 2006 a
) but may be found in other northern Mexican states.

Pacarina championi (
Distant, 1881
)
. The species is known from Mexico , Guatemala , Costa Rica , and Central America (
Metcalf 1963 a
).
